Prevention and early diagnosis of acute pancreatitis after surgery of abdominal organs. Of the 506 patients, operated on the abdominal organs, the clinical signs of acute postoperative pancreatitis (APP) were revealed in 28 (5.5%), stable increase of the amylase activity in the blood-- in 98 (19.4%). Systematic study of the amylase activity in the blood permits to diagnose the mild forms of APP. In high probability of the APP development, its prophylaxis should be started before the operation by means of administration of the protease inhibitors and cytostatic agents.